{"repo": "fonttools/fonttools", "pull_number": 4055, "instance_id": "fonttools__fonttools-4055", "issue_numbers": [4035], "base_commit": "5da76d73514e0b405292ba9809b60d45977632a2", "patch": "diff --git a/Lib/fontTools/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p.py b/Lib/fontTools/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p.py\nindex e935313a18..18d4bc6418 100644\n--- a/Lib/fontTools/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p.py\n+++ b/Lib/fontTools/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p.py\n@@ -204,6 +204,14 @@ def ensureDecompiled(self, recurse=False):\n \n     def compile(self, ttFont):\n         self.tables.sort()  # sort according to the spec; see CmapSubtable.__lt__()\n+        keys = [(t.platformID, t.platEncID, t.language) for t in self.tables]\n+        seen = set()\n+        duplicates = {k for k in keys if k in seen or seen.add(k)}\n+        if duplicates:\n+            raise ValueError(\n+                \"cmap subtables have duplicate (platformID, platEncID, language) \"\n+                f\"entries, which the OpenType spec does not allow: {duplicates}\"\n+            )\n         numSubTables = len(self.tables)\n         totalOffset = 4 + 8 * numSubTables\n         data = struct.pack(\">HH\", self.tableVersion, numSubTables)\n@@ -371,13 +379,11 @@ def __lt__(self, other):\n             getattr(self, \"platformID\", None),\n             getattr(self, \"platEncID\", None),\n             getattr(self, \"language\", None),\n-            self.__dict__,\n         )\n         otherTuple = (\n             getattr(other, \"platformID\", None),\n             getattr(other, \"platEncID\", None),\n             getattr(other, \"language\", None),\n-            other.__dict__,\n         )\n         return selfTuple < otherTuple\n \n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/Tests/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p_test.py b/Tests/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p_test.py\nindex 9bf854e127..45663947c9 100644\n--- a/Tests/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p_test.py\n+++ b/Tests/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p_test.py\n@@ -181,6 +181,34 @@ def test_format_14(self):\n             font.importXML(f)\n         self.assertEqual(font[\"cmap\"].getcmap(0, 5).uvsDict, subtable.uvsDict)\n \n+    def test_sort_subtables_with_duplicate_keys(self):\n+        # https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/issues/4035\n+        # Sorting subtables that share (platformID, platEncID, language) but\n+        # differ in format should not raise TypeError from comparing dicts.\n+        subtable4 = self.makeSubtable(4, 3, 1, 0)\n+        subtable4.cmap = {0x41: \"A\"}\n+        subtable12 = self.makeSubtable(12, 3, 1, 0)\n+        subtable12.cmap = {0x41: \"A\"}\n+        # This used to raise: TypeError: '<' not supported between\n+        # instances of 'dict' and 'dict'\n+        tables = sorted([subtable12, subtable4])\n+        # Both have the same key, so stable sort preserves original order\n+        self.assertEqual(len(tables), 2)\n+\n+    def test_compile_raises_on_duplicate_subtable_keys(self):\n+        # https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/issues/4035\n+        # The OpenType spec requires each (platformID, platEncID, language)\n+        # combination to be unique; compile should raise a clear error.\n+        cmap = table__c_m_a_p()\n+        cmap.tableVersion = 0\n+        subtable4 = self.makeSubtable(4, 3, 1, 0)\n+        subtable4.cmap = {0x41: \"A\"}\n+        subtable12 = self.makeSubtable(12, 3, 1, 0)\n+        subtable12.cmap = {0x41: \"A\"}\n+        cmap.tables = [subtable4, subtable12]\n+        with self.assertRaisesRegex(ValueError, \"duplicate\"):\n+            cmap.compile(ttFont=None)\n+\n \n if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n     import sys\n", "problem_statement": "Inserting new cmap tables will fail on trying to sort them into canonical order\nUnrelated to this issue itself, I am wanting to produce a font which has both a format 4 and a format 12 cmap table from a font that currently has only a format 4 cmap table.\n\nThis script achieves this:\n\n```\nfrom fontTools.ttLib import TTFont\nfrom fontTools.ttLib.tables._c_m_a_p import CmapSubtable\n\n\ndef copy_format4_to_format12(font: TTFont) -> TTFont:\n    \"\"\"\n    Copy all format 4 cmap tables and create format 12 versions of them.\n    \"\"\"\n    cmap = font[\"cmap\"]\n\n    # Collect existing tables to avoid modification during iteration\n    existing_tables = list(cmap.tables)\n\n    for table in existing_tables:\n        if table.format == 4:\n            format12_table = CmapSubtable.newSubtable(12)\n            format12_table.platformID = table.platformID\n            format12_table.platEncID = table.platEncID\n            format12_table.language = table.language\n\n            # Copy the character mappings - this is the crucial part!\n            format12_table.cmap = table.cmap.copy()\n\n            # Manually add to avoid sorting comparison\n            cmap.tables.append(format12_table)\n\n            print(\n                f\"Created format 12 copy of format 4 table (platform {table.platformID}, encoding {table.platEncID}) with {len(format12_table.cmap)} characters\"\n            )\n\n    return font\n\n\ndef main():\n    import sys\n\n    if len(sys.argv) != 3:\n        print(\"Usage: python copy_cmap_format4_to_format12.py input.ttf output.ttf\")\n        return\n\n    input_path = sys.argv[1]\n    output_path = sys.argv[2]\n\n    font = TTFont(input_path)\n    font = copy_format4_to_format12(font)\n    font.save(output_path)\n    print(f\"Saved modified font to {output_path}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n[ConcertOne-Regular.ttf.zip \u2014 I simple open source font with only cmap 4 for testing](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/25043602/ConcertOne-Regular.ttf.zip)\n\nHowever, the script will [fail with a fontTools error pointing to this line](https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/blob/e2fa0c82d1ce4ce63ae7f63325036c43ceb30803/Lib/fontTools/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p.py#L382) with an error message:\n\n>   File \"/Users/johannes/.pyenv/versions/3.12.2/envs/fontsxyz/lib/python3.12/site-packages/fontTools/ttLib/tables/_c_m_a_p.py\", line 372, in __lt__\n    return selfTuple < otherTuple\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: '<' not supported between instances of 'dict' and 'dict'\n\nIf I simply return a boolean to test, the cmaps get written (in arbitrary order of my boolean). I don't know what is the canonical order for saving cmaps, but alternatively, if I remove the `self.__dict__` and `other.__dict__` from the compared tuples, this sorts and writes the cmaps by platform+encoding+language \u2014 which I reckon is entirely sufficient \u2014 why would you need to sort, additionally, by the actual dict of the cmap entries?\n\nNot sure exactly _how construed_ my use case is to begin with, but I reckon many other ways of simply adding cmap tables will fail with the same culprit, e.g. [possibly this sample script](https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/blob/main/Snippets/cmap-format.py) as well.\n", "hints_text": "The code that triggers the error is dodgy: it fails on the `__dict__` comparison once the (platformID, platEncID, language) part is not unique in the list of subtable.\n\nThat said, [the specification says](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/cmap#encoding-records-and-encodings) that each combination of platformID, platEncID, and language must be unique:\n\n> Each platform ID, platform-specific encoding ID, and subtable language combination may appear only once in the 'cmap' table.\n\nSo while the error message is poor due to the dodgy code, the underlying issue is that your list of subtables is invalid.\n(Fun fact, the offending code was [committed by me](https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/commit/7842e56b97ce677b83bdab09cda48bc2d89ac75a#diff-42d5a7d674c9ba1285b0f7d8b65c2f695309bbdd89293f852f7c76037a3baf25) a bit more than 26 years ago... At the time it wasn't yet a bug, as in Python < 3 comparing two dicts did not fail.)\n> So while the error message is poor due to the dodgy code, the underlying issue is that your list of subtables is invalid.\n\nAh, cheers for the additional insight. I see, I just naively tried to create a test font that would reproduce _the other issue_ I'm trying to debug, without having much looked at the combination of plat/enc/lang \u2014 the original proprietary font I'm testing indeed has them differ, it's just my naive copying of the cmap format 4 as format 12 that brought this up.\n\nI still don't quite understand why there would be a need for the additional `__dict__`'s in there for the comparison. Are you saying: \n- it should raise an exception outright when platform, encoding and language are identical, and\n- the `__dict__` should indeed not be part of the sorting comparison\nI think I added the `__dict__` to the comparison tuples with the intention to deterministically sort even if the three main numbers are the same. But then again, this code does not only predate the \"can't do dict < dict\" restriction, it also predates TimSort, Python's stable sort algorithm. I'm pretty sure that the correct fix is to remove `__dict__` from the comparison tuples.\n\nPerhaps the code *should* raise an explicit error in the conflicting case. But this should then happing during table compilation, and not as a side effect of sorting the tables.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "The code that triggers the error is dodgy: it fails on the `__dict__` comparison once the (platformID, platEncID, language) part is not unique in the list of subtable.\n\nThat said, [the specification says](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/cmap#encoding-records-and-encodings) that each combination of platformID, platEncID, and language must be unique:\n\n> Each platform ID, platform-specific encoding ID, and subtable language combination may appear only once in the 'cmap' table.\n\nSo while the error message is poor due to the dodgy code, the underlying issue is that your list of subtables is invalid.\n(Fun fact, the offending code was [committed by me](https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/commit/7842e56b97ce677b83bdab09cda48bc2d89ac75a#diff-42d5a7d674c9ba1285b0f7d8b65c2f695309bbdd89293f852f7c76037a3baf25) a bit more than 26 years ago... At the time it wasn't yet a bug, as in Python < 3 comparing two dicts did not fail.)\n> So while the error message is poor due to the dodgy code, the underlying issue is that your list of subtables is invalid.\n\nAh, cheers for the additional insight. I see, I just naively tried to create a test font that would reproduce _the other issue_ I'm trying to debug, without having much looked at the combination of plat/enc/lang \u2014 the original proprietary font I'm testing indeed has them differ, it's just my naive copying of the cmap format 4 as format 12 that brought this up.\n\nI still don't quite understand why there would be a need for the additional `__dict__`'s in there for the comparison. Are you saying: \n- it should raise an exception outright when platform, encoding and language are identical, and\n- the `__dict__` should indeed not be part of the sorting comparison\nI think I added the `__dict__` to the comparison tuples with the intention to deterministically sort even if the three main numbers are the same. But then again, this code does not only predate the \"can't do dict < dict\" restriction, it also predates TimSort, Python's stable sort algorithm. I'm pretty sure that the correct fix is to remove `__dict__` from the comparison tuples.\n\nPerhaps the code *should* raise an explicit error in the conflicting case. But this should then happing during table compilation, and not as a side effect of sorting the tables.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/commit/a06246b186cf851e6906171c21b20fc90c02d1db", "https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/commit/10dc3d316e9bf116057d31eabc6034c884a5eb69"], "created_at": "2026-03-05T17:39:27Z"}
{"repo": "fonttools/fonttools", "pull_number": 4040, "instance_id": "fonttools__fonttools-4040", "issue_numbers": [4039], "base_commit": "a57c24628d8b27e006d7dc325bc19287bb6c8580", "patch": "diff --git a/Lib/fontTools/cffLib/__init__.py b/Lib/fontTools/cffLib/__init__.py\nindex 4ad724a27a..8ced9c79fc 100644\n--- a/Lib/fontTools/cffLib/__init__.py\n+++ b/Lib/fontTools/cffLib/__init__.py\n@@ -1264,7 +1264,7 @@ def parseBlendList(s):\n             continue\n         name, attrs, content = element\n         blendList = attrs[\"value\"].split()\n-        blendList = [eval(val) for val in blendList]\n+        blendList = [safeEval(val) for val in blendList]\n         valueList.append(blendList)\n     if len(valueList) == 1:\n         valueList = valueList[0]\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Convert eval call to safeEval in CFFLib\nhttps://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/blob/a57c24628d8b27e006d7dc325bc19287bb6c8580/Lib/fontTools/cffLib/__init__.py#L1267\n\nThis is a near-duplicate of the now merged PR https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/pull/1139.\nSeems like safeEval should also work fine as a replacement here (it's also already imported), and without it, there is potential for arbitrary code execution from a maliciously crafted .ttx file. I have a PoC for this if you want it.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/commit/c5052fdb83b03f3f39c7d4a45d1669988949e95b"], "created_at": "2026-02-15T10:56:52Z"}
{"repo": "fonttools/fonttools", "pull_number": 4043, "instance_id": "fonttools__fonttools-4043", "issue_numbers": [4042], "base_commit": "9caa12715c17ca5b846c6a640aaa5d3503fdbaa2", "patch": "diff --git a/Lib/fontTools/svgLib/path/shapes.py b/Lib/fontTools/svgLib/path/shapes.py\nindex 3f22e6c6a3..112d17fd4e 100644\n--- a/Lib/fontTools/svgLib/path/shapes.py\n+++ b/Lib/fontTools/svgLib/path/shapes.py\n@@ -173,6 +173,8 @@ def _parse_ellipse(self, ellipse):\n         self.A(rx, ry, cx - rx, cy, large_arc=1)\n \n     def add_path_from_element(self, el):\n+        if not isinstance(el.tag, str):\n+            return False\n         tag = _strip_xml_ns(el.tag)\n         parse_fn = getattr(self, \"_parse_%s\" % tag.lower(), None)\n         if not callable(parse_fn):\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/Tests/svgLib/path/path_test.py b/Tests/svgLib/path/path_test.py\nindex c92ca68010..5f205275ad 100644\n--- a/Tests/svgLib/path/path_test.py\n+++ b/Tests/svgLib/path/path_test.py\n@@ -52,6 +52,21 @@ def test_fromstring(self):\n \n         assert pen.value == EXPECTED_PEN_COMMANDS\n \n+    def test_xml_comment_ignored(self):\n+        svg_with_comment = b\"\"\"\\\n+<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\">\n+  <!-- a comment -->\n+  <path d=\"M100 100\"/>\n+</svg>\"\"\"\n+        pen = RecordingPen()\n+        svg = SVGPath.fromstring(svg_with_comment)\n+        svg.draw(pen)\n+\n+        assert pen.value == [\n+            (\"moveTo\", ((100.0, 100.0),)),\n+            (\"endPath\", ()),\n+        ]\n+\n     def test_transform(self):\n         pen = RecordingPen()\n         svg = SVGPath.fromstring(SVG_DATA, transform=(1.0, 0, 0, -1.0, 0, 1000))\n", "problem_statement": "SVGPath drawing chokes on comment\nReproducing:\n```python\nfrom fontTools.pens.recordingPen import RecordingPen\nfrom fontTools.svgLib import SVGPath\n\nsvgText = \"\"\"<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\">\n  <!-- a comment -->\n  <path d=\"M100 100\"/>\n</svg>\"\"\"\n\nsvgPath = SVGPath.fromstring(svgText)\nrecPen = RecordingPen()\nsvgPath.draw(recPen)\n```\n\nError:\n```\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"read_svg.py\", line 11, in <module>\n    svgPath.draw(recPen)\n  File \"venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/fontTools/svgLib/path/__init__.py\", line 58, in draw\n    pb.add_path_from_element(el)\n  File \"venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/fontTools/svgLib/path/shapes.py\", line 177, in add_path_from_element\n    tag = _strip_xml_ns(el.tag)\n          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/fontTools/svgLib/path/shapes.py\", line 19, in _strip_xml_ns\n    return tag.split(\"}\", 1)[1] if \"}\" in tag else tag\n                                   ^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: argument of type '_cython_3_0_10.cython_function_or_method' is not iterable\n```\n\nRemoving the SVG comment from svgText makes it work.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/commit/06197442582b967bc06a86073caf4dcc7e1624dc"], "created_at": "2026-02-25T13:07:27Z"}
